Preheat your oven to 120°C/100°C fan/gas mark 2.

Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%grams} into thirds.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Sandwich each @British Chicken Breast{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #cutting board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a saucepan until it's 1-2cm thick.

Season the chicken with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then lay a @Serrano Ham{2%slices} slice over the top.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay in the chicken, ham-side down. Fry until golden brown, ~{5-6%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, transfer to a #baking tray{}, cover with #foil{} and pop into the oven to keep warm.

Meanwhile, add the @Fresh Tagliatelle{200%grams} and broccoli to your pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the saucepan. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Put your (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once hot, add the garlic and cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @Creme Fraiche{150%grams}, @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams} and @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams}. Bring to the boil, then stir in the @Water for the Sauce{150%milliliter(s)} and simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Remove the chicken from your oven and place on a cutting board to rest for a couple of mins.

Add the cooked tagliatelle and broccoli to the creamy sauce, adding a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Share the creamy tagliatelle between your #bowls{}. Thinly slice the chicken and serve on top of the pasta.

Enjoy!